---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="How Proper Tax Planning Can Keep More Money in Your Restaurant Business | Ambit Blog"
  description="Discover the key tax strategies, credits, and deductions every restaurant owner should know — from Section 179 equipment write-offs to the FICA Tip Credit."
>
  <Navbar />

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden" style="background-color: #0F172A; min-height: 520px;">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <img
        src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1517248135467-4c7edcad34c4?w=1800&auto=format&fit=crop&q=80"
        alt="Restaurant interior"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
        style="opacity: 0.18;"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0F172A 0%, #0F172A 55%, #1a4480 100%); opacity: 0.92;"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[500px] h-[500px] rounded-full opacity-[0.06] blur-3xl" style="background: #1a4480;"></div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-28">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-8 text-xs" style="color: #64748B;">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Blog</a>
        <svg class="w-3 h-3" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        <span style="color: #94A3B8;">Tax Planning</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Category + meta -->
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-white" style="background-color: #059669;">Tax Planning</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color: #64748B;">April 15, 2026</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full" style="background-color: #334155;"></span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color: #64748B;">7 min read</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-white mb-6" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        How Proper Tax Planning Can Keep More Money in Your Restaurant Business
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: #94A3B8; max-width: 640px;">
        Discover the key tax strategies, credits, and deductions every restaurant owner should know — from Section 179 equipment write-offs to the FICA Tip Credit.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== ARTICLE BODY ===== -->
  <section class="py-20" style="background-color: #ffffff;">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-14 items-start">

        <!-- Main Content -->
        <article>

          <!-- Intro -->
          <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6" style="color: #374151;">
            Running a restaurant can be very fulfilling and challenging at the same time — especially when navigating the tax issues involved in every restaurant operation. A knowledgeable tax professional can provide the information needed to help restaurant owners start saving on taxes and keep more of their hard-earned earnings.
          </p>
          <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-10" style="color: #64748B;">
            Restaurants have distinct tax challenges and opportunities which makes it critical to tap into every available strategy to optimise tax outcomes. At Ambit, we specialise in helping restaurants keep their books in good order and prepare for tax time efficiently.
          </p>

          <!-- Divider -->
          <div class="w-12 h-1 rounded mb-12" style="background-color: #1a4480;"></div>

          <!-- Section 1 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">1</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Deduct the Full Value of Eligible Equipment and Improvements</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">
              Most restaurants invest in new equipment and physical improvements to keep up with consumer expectations and industry standards. Expenses of this nature can generally be written off through accelerated depreciation.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-4 pl-4">
              <div class="p-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0; border-left: 3px solid #1a4480;">
                <div class="text-sm font-bold mb-1" style="color: #0F172A;">Section 179 Deduction</div>
                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">Authorises taxpayers to write down the entire purchase price of qualifying assets — including fixtures and equipment assigned to the business — in the year of purchase, subject to limitations.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="p-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0; border-left: 3px solid #1a4480;">
                <div class="text-sm font-bold mb-1" style="color: #0F172A;">Bonus Depreciation (Section 168)</div>
                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">Business-use property without prior pretax value may qualify for immediate deductions under bonus depreciation provisions.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="p-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0; border-left: 3px solid #1a4480;">
                <div class="text-sm font-bold mb-1" style="color: #0F172A;">Cost Segregation Studies</div>
                <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">When acquiring or repositioning a property, cost segregation studies can reclassify certain building components into shorter-lived depreciation categories, accelerating deductions.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 2 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">2</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Understand and Maximise Available Tax Credits</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5" style="color: #64748B;">
              Tax credits reduce your tax obligation directly — making them among the most powerful tools available to restaurant owners. Key credits include:
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              {[
                { title: 'FICA Tip Credit', desc: 'Restaurants must bear FICA taxes for reported tips. This credit provides cost recovery for tips above the minimum wage threshold ($5.15/hr under this credit), delivering significant savings.' },
                { title: 'Work Opportunity Tax Credit (WOTC)', desc: 'Hiring employees from target groups — like veterans and long-term unemployed individuals — can generate substantial credits, consistently lowering tax liabilities for qualifying restaurants.' },
                { title: 'Qualified Business Income (QBI) Deduction', desc: 'Owners of pass-through entities (LLCs, S Corporations, partnerships) may be able to deduct up to 20% of qualified business income, meaningfully reducing effective tax rates.' },
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="flex gap-4 p-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
                  <svg class="w-5 h-5 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" style="color: #059669;"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                  <div>
                    <div class="text-sm font-bold mb-1" style="color: #0F172A;">{item.title}</div>
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">{item.desc}</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 3 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">3</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Proper Worker Classification to Avoid Costly Penalties</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5" style="color: #64748B;">
              Misclassification of employees and contractors is one of the most common problems in the restaurant sector, leading to audits and penalties. Proper classification is essential for tax planning and compliance.
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Consider the degree of control exercised over workers — time, tasks, and equipment usage.',
                'Apply the correct tax forms: W-2 for employees and 1099 for independent contractors.',
                'Maintain accurate records to reduce exposure during tax filing and audit scenarios.',
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 mt-2" style="background-color: #1a4480;"></div>
                  <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">{item}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 4 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">4</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Reserve for Quarterly Tax Payments</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">
              Restaurants operate on slim margins with fluctuating profit. Failing to plan for quarterly tax payments brings fines and additional financial stress. Whether your restaurant is structured as an S Corporation, LLC, or sole proprietorship, advance planning is essential. Set aside a portion of gains for quarterly payments and work with a tax professional to project accurate amounts and manage the cash flow challenges associated with seasonal peaks.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 5 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">5</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Deduct Routine Repairs and Maintenance</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">
              Capitalising a minor repair instead of expensing it means losing out on potential deductions. The IRS Repair Regulations provide that:
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Routine maintenance and ordinary repairs that don\'t materially extend the life of equipment or a building can be expensed immediately.',
                'Scrutinising maintenance expenses can surface deductions that meaningfully lower overall tax liability.',
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 mt-2" style="background-color: #1a4480;"></div>
                  <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">{item}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Section 6 -->
          <div class="mb-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
              <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0 text-sm font-black text-white" style="background-color: #1a4480;">6</div>
              <h2 class="text-xl font-bold" style="color: #0F172A;">Modify Your Business Structure for Long-Term Tax Savings</h2>
            </div>
            <p class="text-base leading-relaxed mb-5" style="color: #64748B;">
              The type of business entity you operate under significantly impacts your tax position. Key considerations:
            </p>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              {[
                { label: 'C Corporations', desc: 'Subject to double taxation — once at the corporate level and again when dividends are distributed.' },
                { label: 'S Corporations', desc: 'Allow owners to avoid self-employment taxes by taking a portion of income as distributions rather than wages.' },
                { label: 'Partnerships', desc: 'Pass income through to partners and may allow for QBI deduction eligibility.' },
              ].map(item => (
                <div class="flex gap-3 p-4 rounded-xl" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
                  <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full flex-shrink-0 mt-2" style="background-color: #1a4480;"></div>
                  <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;"><span class="font-semibold" style="color: #0F172A;">{item.label}:</span> {item.desc}</p>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Why Start Now callout -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #EFF6FF, #F0FDF4); border: 1px solid #BFDBFE;">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3" style="color: #0F172A;">Why Start Tax Planning Now?</h3>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3" style="color: #374151;">
              The beginning of tax season may seem overwhelming, but early planning sets your restaurant up for success. By organising documentation, identifying eligible credits and deductions, and ensuring proper classification of workers and expenses, you can avoid last-minute stress, reduce errors, and improve the accuracy of your return.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #374151;">
              Investing in professional guidance tailored to the restaurant industry — like the services provided by Ambit — can help you capture every available tax-saving opportunity. Staying proactive not only minimises your current tax liability but also positions your business for long-term financial health.
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- FAQs -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-8" style="color: #0F172A; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4" x-data="{ open: null }">
              {[
                { q: 'Why is tax planning important for restaurant owners?', a: 'Tax planning helps restaurant owners reduce tax liabilities, maximise deductions, and stay compliant with tax regulations, ultimately improving cash flow and profitability.' },
                { q: 'What tax credits are available for restaurants?', a: 'Key tax credits include the FICA Tip Credit and the Work Opportunity Tax Credit (WOTC), both of which can significantly reduce tax obligations.' },
                { q: 'How can quarterly tax payments help restaurant owners?', a: 'Reserving funds for quarterly tax payments avoids penalties and reduces financial strain by spreading tax obligations throughout the year.' },
                { q: 'What types of expenses qualify for routine maintenance and repair deductions?', a: 'Expenses for routine maintenance and minor repairs that don\'t extend the life of assets can be expensed immediately to reduce tax liability.' },
                { q: 'When should restaurants start tax planning?', a: 'Early tax planning helps organise records, identify deductions, avoid errors, and ensure compliance, minimising last-minute stress and maximising savings.' },
                { q: 'Why is proper worker classification important for restaurants?', a: 'Misclassifying employees and contractors can lead to penalties and audits. Accurate classification ensures compliance and smooth tax filing.' },
              ].map((faq, i) => (
                <div class="rounded-xl overflow-hidden" style="border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
                  <button
                    class="w-full flex items-center justify-between px-5 py-4 text-left"
                    style="background-color: #F8FAFC;"
                    @click={`open === ${i} ? open = null : open = ${i}`}
                  >
                    <span class="text-sm font-semibold pr-4" style="color: #0F172A;">{faq.q}</span>
                    <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform" :class={`open === ${i} ? 'rotate-180' : ''`} style="color: #64748B;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                      <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
                    </svg>
                  </button>
                  <div x-show={`open === ${i}`} x-transition style="display:none;" class="px-5 py-4" style="background-color: #ffffff; border-top: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
                    <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">{faq.a}</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

        </article>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="hidden lg:block" style="position: sticky; top: 96px;">

          <!-- Author box -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 mb-6" style="background-color: #0F172A; border: 1px solid #1E293B;">
            <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">About Ambit</div>
            <p class="text-xs leading-relaxed mb-5" style="color: #94A3B8;">
              Ambit is a trusted provider of accounting, tax, and business advisory services for CPA firms, small businesses, and individuals across the US, UK, and UAE. Over 8 years of experience.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 w-full py-2.5 text-xs font-semibold text-white rounded-lg" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a4480, #1e5ab5);">
              Book Free Consultation
            </a>
          </div>

          <!-- Categories -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6 mb-6" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
            <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">Topics</div>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              {['Tax Planning', 'Accounting', 'Payroll', 'Restaurant', 'US Business', 'Compliance'].map(tag => (
                <span class="text-xs font-medium px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full" style="background-color: #EFF6FF; color: #1a4480; border: 1px solid #BFDBFE;">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Key takeaways -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl p-6" style="background-color: #F8FAFC; border: 1px solid #E2E8F0;">
            <div class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">Key Takeaways</div>
            <div class="space-y-3">
              {[
                'Use Section 179 to write off equipment costs faster',
                'FICA Tip Credit can generate significant savings',
                'Correct worker classification prevents audits',
                'Plan for quarterly payments to avoid penalties',
                'Entity structure directly impacts tax liability',
              ].map(point => (
                <div class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
                  <svg class="w-4 h-4 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" style="color: #1a4480;"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                  <span class="text-xs leading-relaxed" style="color: #64748B;">{point}</span>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== CTA ===== -->
  <section class="py-20" style="background-color: #0F172A;">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4" style="color: #64748B;">Get Expert Help</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-black text-white mb-5" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
        Ready to Reduce Your Restaurant's Tax Burden?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-base mb-10" style="color: #94A3B8;">
        Our tax specialists work with restaurant owners across the US to identify every available saving — so you keep more of what you earn.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 text-sm font-bold text-white rounded-lg transition-all hover:opacity-90" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a4480, #1e5ab5);">
          Book Free Consultation
          <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-8 py-4 text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg border transition-all hover:bg-white/5" style="color: #94A3B8; border-color: #334155;">
          More Articles
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
